<br>
------------<br>
<br>
Now, would a NLB GCNR work? Yes, if designed properly, and if operated in SPACE, not from the ground. Designs by the experts have operating conditions an order of magnitude lower - but at a realistic thrust to weight ratio it would never lift its own weight. In space it would zoom like a champ (and not cause a radiological disaster in an accident).<br>
<br>
